TY  - JOUR
T1  - Who Matters to Ceos? An Investigation of Stakeholder Attributes and Salience, Corpate Performance, and Ceo Values
AU  - Agle, Bradley R.
AU  - Mitchell, Ronald K.
AU  - Sonnenfeld, Jeffrey A.
Y1  - 1999/10/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256973
DO  - 10.5465/256973
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 507
EP  - 525
VL  - 42
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Using unique data provided by the CEOs of 80 large U.S. firms, the authors examined relationships among the stakeholder attributes of power, legitimacy, urgency, and salience; CEO values; and corporate performance. They found strong support for the attribute-salience relationship and some significant relationships among CEO values, salience, and corporate social performance but found no support for a salience-financial performance link. Their findings suggest a need for continued emphasis on the development of normative stakeholder theory.
AB  - Using unique data provided by the CEOs of 80 large U.S. firms, the authors examined relationships among the stakeholder attributes of power, legitimacy, urgency, and salience; CEO values; and corporate performance. They found strong support for the attribute-salience relationship and some significant relationships among CEO values, salience, and corporate social performance but found no support for a salience-financial performance link. Their findings suggest a need for continued emphasis on the development of normative stakeholder theory.
